President Barack Obama has proclaimed September 2011 as National Preparedness Month in the United States. The proclamation highlights the importance of preparedness and collaboration in disaster response. The proclamation also mentions recent natural disasters that have tested the country's response ability, such as tornadoes and Hurricane Irene. The President emphasizes that preparedness is a shared responsibility and encourages individuals to join together and share information through the National Preparedness Month Coalition. The proclamation concludes by urging Americans to work together to enhance national security, resilience, and readiness.